ir own distinctive physiology predicated on understanding animal functions in a context of environmental adaptation and evolutionary forces. Physiological schools with distinct emphases that shaped their outlook sprang up around the world. Dividing their time between fieldwork in marine stations and laboratory experimentation, animal physiologists stood in awe of the diversity and ingenuity of the functional strategies by which animals survived.Animal as Machine tells a remarkable and insightful story of the larger-than-life personalities and gripping historical episodes that marked the emergence and blossoming of animal physiology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPhysiologistsxHistory. 0aPhysiologyxHistory. 7aSCIENCE / History.2bisacsh  aBelgian School.  aBernd Heinrich.  aBodil Schmidt-Nielsen.  aBrains.  aC Ladd Prosser.  aCharles Darwin.  aEdward Stuart Russell.  aEric Kandel.  aFish.  aGeorges Cuvier.  aHistory.  aIntegrative.  aMetabolism.  aNaples Zoological Station.  aNeural.  aSteven Pinker.  aWilliam Hoar.  aWoods Hole.  aadaptation.  aanatomy.  abiology.  acomparative biochemistry.  aenvironment.  aevolution.  aform.  afunctional.  alearning.  amodification.  aphysiology.  ascience.  astructure.  asurvival.  azoophysiology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780228012214?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228012214423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228012214/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter